description: Number of partitions of 4*n into four odd primes (p_1, p_2, p_3, p_4) (p_1 < p_2 <= p_3 < p_4 and p_1 + p_4 = p_2 + p_3 = 2*n) such that (p_1, p_2) and (p_3, p_4) are consecutive pairs of prime numbers with the same difference, d = p_2 - p_1 = p_4 - p_3, and (p_1, p_3), (p_2, p_4) are also consecutive pairs of prime numbers with the same difference, D = p_3 - p_1 = p_4 - p_2.
